  "response": "During the time of Prophet Muhammad, the Jewish tribes that lived in Macca and Madinah (then known as Yathrib) were primarily from the tribes of Banu Nadir, Banu Qurayzah, and Banu Qaynuqa. These tribes were mainly settled in and around Madinah, not in Macca. They were predominantly Arab Jews who had established settlements in the region before the arrival of Islam. These tribes had significant economic and social influence in the area and initially had various political and commercial relationships with the local Arab tribes before coming into conflict with Prophet Muhammad and the early Muslim community.",
